The new Premier League season enters its fourth Match Day this weekend. Manchester United will be hoping to bounce back from a shock 2-1 loss to Crystal Palace, when they travel to Southampton in Saturday’s early kick-off. Chelsea host Sheffield United, Manchester City play Brighton and Bournemouth are away to Leicester City. The late kick-off will see Burnley welcome table toppers Liverpool. Saturday, August 31
12:30 Southampton vs Manchester United
15:00 Chelsea vs Sheffield United
15:00 Crystal Palace vs Aston Villa
15:00 Leicester City vs AFC Bournemouth
15:00 Manchester City vs Brighton & Hove Albion
15:00 Newcastle United vs Watford
15:00 West Ham United vs Norwich City
